OL,12,FTo live in temporary accommodation is
OL,13,Fto live in constant uncertainty. Your
OL,14,Fhome is not your own, and could be
OL,15,Ftaken away from you in an instant.
OL,17,FThe phone may ring, or an email may
OL,18,Fland in your inbox, that uproots your
OL,19,Fwhole life; demanding you pack up all
OL,20,Fyour belongings and move on, often
OL,21,Fwith less than a days notice.
